One Pot Chicken with Dates & Caramelized Lemon

**blatantly stolen from Alison Roman's Nothing Fancy, pg. 194**

  - 3 lbs bone-in skin-on chicken thighs
  - 2 tbsp olive oil
  - 1 lemon, cut into thick slices crosswise, seeds removed
  - 3-4 shallots, halved lengthwise
  - 5-7 medjool dates, pitted
  - 4 sprigs thyme
  - 1 cup water
  - 2 tsp ground Urfa chile (or 1 tsp crushed red pepper flake)

  (1) Preheat oven to 425 degrees F
  (2) Season chicken, sear in a large dutch oven. Let sit for 5-8 minutes wo moving skin side down!
  (3) Add lemon slices & shallots, moving chicken as needed to make sure lemon is on the surface of the dutch oven, sizzle for 2 min
  (4) Add dates, thyme, and water.
  (5) Sprinkle the top of chicken w Urfa chile and put the lid on the Dutch oven. Place in oven for 20-25 min.
  (6) Remove lid and drizzle chicken w olive oil, and continue to cook until liquid has reduced by half and the chicken is golden brown on top, perhaps another 25 min.
   
